decision_conditions:
Condition : 3 - Prior to commencement of groundworks (excluding site investigations and demolition), the applicant shall have submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in writing, details and samples of the materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted. 

The samples/details shall include: 

 	Brick (including brick detail, soldier coursing, mortar colours, joint type, brick bond and sample panels a minimum size of 1m x 1m); 
 	Roofing material, stone cills, cladding and balcony decking and balustrades;
 	Doors and window treatments (including sections and reveals) and;
 	Any other materials/details to be used.


The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.
